## Step 1 — Confirm what the virtual repo actually serves (the one test that settles it)

Run this from the bastion or any host that reaches Artifactory, using the **same** `JF_USER` / `JF_TOKEN` the pipeline uses:

```bash
# The PLUGIN MARKER — this is the exact artifact the build couldn't resolve
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "MARKER: %{http_code}\n" -u "$JF_USER:$JF_TOKEN" \
"https://artifactory.jfrog.sbi:443/artifactory/itepaypg-sbiepay2-gradle-virtual/org/springframework/boot/org.springframework.boot.gradle.plugin/3.5.9/org.springframework.boot.gradle.plugin-3.5.9.pom"

# The BOM/dependency artifact — this is almost certainly what you're seeing in the JFrog UI
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "BOM:    %{http_code}\n" -u "$JF_USER:$JF_TOKEN" \
"https://artifactory.jfrog.sbi:443/artifactory/itepaypg-sbiepay2-gradle-virtual/org/springframework/boot/spring-boot-dependencies/3.5.9/spring-boot-dependencies-3.5.9.pom"
